      • get

        @Suspendable
public static <E> LocalQueue<E> get​(java.lang.String name,
                                    int capacity)
        Description copied from interface: SuspendableQueue
        Gets a reference to a bounded queue with the specified name.

        If a capacity > 0 is specified, the queue is bounded.

        If the queue does not exist, it will be created when any SuspendableQueue.offer(Object) is called with createQueue == true; or, if a SuspendableQueue.poll(long) is ever called.

        Type Parameters:
        E - The type of the items.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the queue shared in the cluster
        capacity - The bounded capacity (SuspendableQueue.offer(Object) will return false if the bound is exceeded), or if 0 or negative, no bound is specified.
        Returns:
        A reference to a suspendable queue. Until a method is called on it, its underlying data structures in the cluster may not be created.
        See Also:
        for an unbounded version of this method.

      • destroy

        @Suspendable
public void destroy()
        Description copied from interface: SuspendableQueue
        Destroys the queue.

        Destroying the queue does not interrupt existing calls to SuspendableQueue.poll(long).

        Once the queue is destroyed, its backing datastructures in the cluster are removed.

        Specified by:
